'''安妮·卡森'''（{{lang-en|Anne Carson}}，{{bd|1950年|6月21日}}）是一名[[加拿大|加拿大]]詩人、作家、[[古典學|古典學家]]、古典文獻翻譯家，曾任教於[[麥基爾大學|麥基爾大學]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news-archive.mcgill.ca/w97/poet.htm |title=McGill News - Winter '97 |publisher=News-archive.mcgill.ca |accessdate=2010-10-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104062705/http://news-archive.mcgill.ca/w97/poet.htm |archive-date=2013-11-04 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>、[[密西根大學|密西根大學]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.phf.upenn.edu/09-10/carson.shtml |title=Penn Humanities Forum | Anne Carson |publisher=Phf.upenn.edu |date=2009-12-02 |accessdate=2010-10-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100618221630/http://www.phf.upenn.edu/09-10/carson.shtml |archivedate=2010-06-18 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>、[[普林斯頓大學|普林斯頓大學]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.poets.org/poet.php/prmPID/317 |title=Anne Carson- Poets.org - Poetry, Poems, Bios & More |publisher=Poets.org |date=1950-06-21 |accessdate=2010-10-28 |archive-date=2014-03-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140310063044/http://www.poets.org/poet.php/prmPID/317 |dead-url=no }}</ref>和[[巴德學院|巴德學院]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bard.edu/news/releases/pr/fstory.php?id=2563|title=Esteemed Writer Anne Carson To Join Bard College Faculty|publisher=Bard College|date=2014-04-29|access-date=2020-06-28|archive-date=2020-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200915185155/https://www.bard.edu/news/releases/pr/fstory.php?id=2563|dead-url=no}}</ref>。卡森曾獲得過的主要獎項包括[[古根海姆獎|古根海姆獎]]（1998）<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gf.org/fellows/2333-anne-carson |title=Anne Carson - John Simon Guggenheim Memorial Foundation |publisher=Gf.org |date= |accessdate=2010-10-28 |archive-date=2014-08-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140823134759/http://www.gf.org/fellows/2333-anne-carson |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[麥克阿瑟獎|麥克阿瑟獎]]（2000）<ref>{{cite web |title="Anne Carson" |url=https://www.macfound.org/fellows/634/ |website=MacArthur Foundation |accessdate=2020-06-28 |archive-date=2020-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109162135/https://www.macfound.org/fellows/634/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>與[[阿斯圖里亞斯親王獎|阿斯圖里亞斯親王獎]]（2020）<ref>{{cite web|title=Anne Carson, Princess of Asturias Award for Literature 2020|publisher=Princess of Asturias Foundation|url=https://www.fpa.es/en/princess-of-asturias-awards/laureates/2020-anne-carson.html|accessdate=18 June 2020|archive-date=2020-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200915204531/https://www.fpa.es/en/princess-of-asturias-awards/laureates/2020-anne-carson.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==生平==
卡森畢業於[[多倫多大學|多倫多大學]]（[[學士|學士]]、[[碩士|碩士]]、[[博士|博士]]）<ref>"Classic Carson". {{cite web|author=Val Ross|url=http://www.magazine.utoronto.ca/01spring/carson.asp|title=University of Toronto Magazine|volume=Spring 2001|access-date=2018-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070823013108/http://www.magazine.utoronto.ca/01spring/carson.asp|archive-date=2007-08-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>，又在[[聖安德魯大學|聖安德魯大學]]專攻古希臘[[韻律|韻律]]研究與[[文本批判|文本批判]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scottishreviewofbooks.org/index.php?option=com_kunena&func=view&catid=18&id=185&Itemid=122|title=Scottish Review of Books}}</ref>，其後以古典學教授的身份開始寫作詩歌與散文。其曾翻譯的古代文學作品包括[[艾斯奇勒斯|艾斯奇勒斯]]的《[[俄瑞斯忒亞|阿伽門農]]》、[[索福克勒斯|索福克勒斯]]的《厄勒克特拉》與[[歐里庇得斯|歐里庇得斯]]的《俄瑞斯忒斯》，三部英譯話劇都在紐約{{tsl|en|Classic Stage Company|古典舞臺劇團}}上演。2015年，卡森譯本[[索福克勒斯|索福克勒斯]]的《[[安蒂岡妮_(索福克勒斯版)|安蒂岡妮]]》在倫敦[[巴比肯藝術中心|巴比肯藝術中心]]上演，女主角由[[茱麗葉·畢諾許|茱麗葉·畢諾許]]擔任<ref>{{cite news |author1=Charlotte Higgins |title="Death becomes her: how Juliette Binoche and Ivo van Hove remade Antigone" |url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2015/feb/18/juliette-binoche-ivo-van-hove-antigone |accessdate=2020-06-28 |work=[[衛報|The Guardian]] |date=2015-02-18 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108115943/http://www.theguardian.com/stage/2015/feb/18/juliette-binoche-ivo-van-hove-antigone |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2010到2016年間，卡森在[[康奈爾大學|康奈爾大學]]出任編外教授（{{lang|en|professor-at-large}}）<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://adwhiteprofessors.cornell.edu/all-professors-at-large-1965-to-june-30-20222/|title=All Professors at Large 1965 to June 30, 2023|website=Cornell University|access-date=8 June 2018|archive-date=2018-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615031244/http://adwhiteprofessors.cornell.edu/all-professors-at-large-1965-to-june-30-20222/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，其後在[[紐約大學|紐約大學]]任駐留藝術家（{{lang|en|artist-in-residence}}）至今<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cwp.fas.nyu.edu/object/carsonsimic.html |title=NYU > CWP > Anne Carson, Charles Simic Join Faculty |publisher=Cwp.fas.nyu.edu |date= |accessdate=2010-10-28 |archive-date=2011-07-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720015503/http://cwp.fas.nyu.edu/object/carsonsimic.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==著作==
1986年，卡森出版其第一部散文集，名爲《厄洛斯與甜蜜的痛苦》（''Eros the Bittersweet''）。該書中卡森以[[莎芙|莎芙]]把愛情（[[厄洛斯|厄洛斯]]）稱作「甜蜜的痛苦」這一有名殘篇出發，從古希臘詩歌着手分析古希臘人對愛情的世界觀，其中包括對莎芙的詩中「慾望的三角性」「慾望的模仿性」以及厄洛斯與孤獨的關係等論點。對卡森來說，愛或厄洛斯在莎芙的詩中是「遷延的、被悖逆的、被阻止的、飢餓的，它圍繞一個光輝的不在場來展開——將厄洛斯以缺失呈現。」<ref>"... eros as deferred, defied, obstructed, hungry, organized around a radiant absence – to represent eros as lack." 出自 {{Cite book|title = Eros the Bittersweet|url = https://books.google.com/books?id=BsY3SXlXORAC|publisher = Dalkey Archive Press|date = 1986-01-01|isbn = 9781564781888|language = en|first = Anne|last = Carson|access-date = 2018-06-09|archive-date = 2020-05-19|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200519030927/https://books.google.com/books?id=BsY3SXlXORAC|dead-url = no}}</ref>該書在{{tsl|en|Modern Library|現代圖書館}}書社讀者評選的史上100佳非虛構作品名單中排行第57名<ref>{{cite web |title=Book awards: The Modern Library's 100 Best Nonfiction: The Reader's List |url=https://www.librarything.com/bookaward/The+Modern+Library%27s+100+Best+Nonfiction%3A+The+Reader%27s+List |website=Library Thing |accessdate=2020-06-28 |archive-date=2020-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201219090124/http://www.librarything.com/bookaward/The+Modern+Library%27s+100+Best+Nonfiction%3A+The+Reader%27s+List |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

此外，卡森出版于1998年的《{{tsl|en|Autography of Red|紅的自傳}}》改編自抒情詩人[[斯特西克魯斯|斯特西克魯斯]]的殘篇，以韻文小說的形式作成。該書受到了[[艾麗斯·孟若|艾麗斯·孟若]]與[[蘇珊·桑塔格|蘇珊·桑塔格]]等文學批判家的好評，並以兩年內超過25000本的銷量成爲當代詩界罕見的暢銷書之一<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://thewalrus.ca/myth-interpretation/|title=Myth Interpretation|last=Liss|first=Sarah|date=March 11, 2003|work=The Walrus|access-date=February 2, 2020|archive-date=2020-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919050752/https://thewalrus.ca/myth-interpretation/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

